--- a/dist/selection-C4e-Qn9W.js
+++ b/dist/selection-C4e-Qn9W.js

Changes made:

1. Added isValidThinkingSignature(signature) function
   - Validates signature is non-empty string
   - Validates base64 format regex
   - Validates decoded byte length is 32-512 bytes

2. Updated hasReplayableThinkingSignature(block) to use isValidThinkingSignature
   - Instead of bare `typeof === "string" && trim().length > 0`
   - Now checks base64 validity and byte length range

3. Updated stripInvalidThinkingSignatures(messages, options)
   - Removed the `preserveLatestAssistant` skip (lines 18-20 in original)
   - Now validates ALL thinking blocks including latest assistant message
   - Invalid signatures are stripped from ALL messages

Behavior change: Previously, latest assistant message thinking blocks
were unconditionally preserved. Now, thinking blocks with invalid
signatures (empty, non-base64, wrong byte length) are stripped even
from the latest assistant message.
